snippet.textDisplay: None of us walk this world as perfect human beings. But those of us who’ve been lucky enough to be parents understand this... our kids think we are the most strongest, smartest, fearless, and perfect human beings they will ever know. I can’t imagine the fear that existed in that helicopter. But I can surely bet that he held his daughter... and promised her that it would be ok... and as doubtful as he knew himself to be.... she believed in him...
